# WANTED engine — top-level configuration.
#
# This is what `just menuconfig` opens, and the only file that sees the whole
# tree. It exists to keep one menu over two files with different audiences:
#
#   Kconfig.target   how to build it — target, board, SDK. Build-system only;
#                    never reaches the compiler.
#   Kconfig.engine   what the binary is. Host-agnostic, and sourced directly by
#                    hosts that compile engine sources into their own tree
#                    (NuttX, ESP-IDF) — they answer the target question by
#                    construction, so they must not be asked it again.
#
# wanted-autoconf.h is generated from Kconfig.engine alone, while .config spans
# this tree. That is what keeps an SDK URL out of the binary while leaving both
# menus in one place.

mainmenu "WANTED Engine Configuration"

source "Kconfig.target"
source "Kconfig.engine"
